<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I used writeroom-mode for hours and find the &quot;distraction-free writing mode&quot; is amazing.</p> <p>Then it comes to me that a standard mode-line mode provides unnecessary noisy messages such as major mode, file name which I absolutely know.</p> <p>How could set it as simple as a black separate lineï¼š</p> <p><a href="https://preview.redd.it/xidckjtqga0b1.png?width=724&amp;format=png&amp;auto=webp&amp;s=f4e5422448988b1253b297d5ee4acf104e6b02a9">https://preview.redd.it/xidckjtqga0b1.png?width=724&amp;format=png&amp;auto=webp&amp;s=f4e5422448988b1253b297d5ee4acf104e6b02a9</a></p> <p>I tried as:</p> <pre><code>(setq mode-line-format writeroom-mode-line) ;; the above dispaly the same as the below (setq mode-line-format nil) </code></pre> <p>The mode-line vanished even without a separate line.</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/AbstProcDo"> /u/AbstProcDo </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/13jmmq8/how_set_modelineformat_as_simple_as_a_horizontal/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/emacs/comments/13jmmq8/how_set_modelineformat_as_simple_as_a_horizontal/">[comments]</a></span>